      "side": 1,
      "message": "[critical] Line 78: 🟡 `fromJson` does not validate `localHost`. A malicious or corrupted JSON file could set `localHost` to an arbitrary hostname/IP (e.g. `0.0.0.0` or a remote address), causing the tunnel handler to connect to unintended hosts. Consider validating that `localHost` is a loopback address (`127.0.0.1` or `::1`) to prevent SSRF-like issues when the tunnel connects outbound.\n\n```suggestion\n    r.localHost \u003d v.get(\"localHost\", \"127.0.0.1\").asString();\n    if (r.localHost !\u003d \"127.0.0.1\" \u0026\u0026 r.localHost !\u003d \"::1\" \u0026\u0026 r.localHost !\u003d \"localhost\") {\n        JAMI_WARNING(\"[ServiceManager] rejecting non-loopback localHost: {}\", r.localHost);\n        return false;\n    }\n```",
      "revId": "3662bf671fe456bafeed1c1f2bd8eb3335f9487f",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
