      "message": "Line 33: 🟡 `MsgType` constants are `const char*` pointers, which means every comparison requires `strcmp`-style matching. Since `peekType` already returns `std::string`, consider making these `constexpr std::string_view` for type safety and to enable `\u003d\u003d` comparisons without implicit conversion.\n\n```suggestion\nconstexpr std::string_view kQuery            \u003d \"query\";\nconstexpr std::string_view kServiceList      \u003d \"service_list\";\nconstexpr std::string_view kError            \u003d \"error\";\nconstexpr std::string_view kVersionMismatch  \u003d \"version_mismatch\";\n```",
