      "message": "Line 120: 🔴 `onRequest` captures `acc` (a `shared_ptr\u003cJamiAccount\u003e`) by reference in the lambda passed to `isAuthorized`. This is safe here because the lambda doesn\u0027t outlive the scope, but the pattern is fragile — if `isAuthorized` ever stores the checker, it would dangle. Use a value capture for safety:\n\n```suggestion\n    auto checker \u003d [acc](const std::string\u0026 uri) { return acc-\u003eisConfirmedContact(uri); };\n```",
