      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 176: 🟡 `async_write` to the TCP socket is fire-and-forget — errors in the completion handler are only logged, not propagated back. If the TCP write fails, the channel continues forwarding data into a broken socket. The error handler should shut down the channel socket to stop the flow:\n\n```suggestion\n                              [buf, channelKeep](const std::error_code\u0026 ec, std::size_t) {\n                                  if (ec) {\n                                      JAMI_DEBUG(\"[SvcTunnel] write to TCP failed: {}\", ec.message());\n                                      channelKeep-\u003eshutdown();\n                                  }\n                              });\n```",
      "revId": "3662bf671fe456bafeed1c1f2bd8eb3335f9487f",
